Despite the unprecedented market conditions in January, at the end of the day, what happened was not acceptable to us. To our customers, we apologize, and we‚Äôve taken steps to make sure this won‚Äôt happen again.
Robinhood immediately secured additional funds. We have increased our liquidity by $3.4 billion to cushion against increased collateral requirements and related market stress. https://t.co/4gcfY5PCBa

No one outside of Robinhood asked or commanded us to take this action. We don‚Äôt answer to hedge funds. We serve the millions of small investors who use our platform every day to take control of their financial future.

For perspective, on Jan. 28, our daily deposit requirement was 10 times more than Jan 25, an unprecedented amount for the firm. So we had to impose temporary trading restrictions on certain securities. https://t.co/8T1r8jcN2f
Our clearing broker Robinhood Securities was required to post additional firm capital as collateral to support our clearing house deposit demands.

In late January, many brokerages saw a massive increase in trading activity in a handful of stocks. Prices were moving dramatically day-to-day and even hour-to-hour. Jan 28 proved to be a completely unprecedented event.
Many people tell us Robinhood has helped them pay off car loans, reduce student loan debt, meet daily bills and save for the future. We‚Äôre proud to serve them.

Today the total value of our customers‚Äô assets on Robinhood excessed the net amount of money they have deposited with us by over $35 billion. While the markets fluctuate, this tells me that our business model is working for everyday Americans. This is the Robinhood community.

With features like fractional shares, dividend reinvestments, and recurring investments our customers can start with small amounts and grow their investments over time.
Contrary to some very misleading and highly uninformed reports, we see evidence that most of our customers are investing for the long-term.
The stock market is a powerful wealth creator, but barely half of U.S. households participate in it. We created Robinhood to economically empower all Americans by opening financial markets to them.

Robinhood was founded on the belief that the financial system should be built to work for everyone, not just a select few. We dreamed of making investing more accessible, especially for people without a lot of money.
